      "evidence": [
        "goseg/importer/importer.go splits runtime into `importerConfigRuntime`, `importerUploadRuntime`, and `importerProvisionRuntime`, but each contains many callback fields and large nil-validation ladders (lines ~170-261).",
        "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go similarly models startup as callback-heavy structs (`startupInitCoreSubsystemRuntime`, `startupBootstrapRuntimeFns`) with explicit missing-callback audits rather than cohesive service contracts.",
        "goseg/main.go introduces another callback bag (`bootstrapRuntime`) and merge logic (`resolveBootstrapRuntime`) that repeats the same DI style instead of reusing a stable abstraction."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Replace callback bags with a small set of role-focused interfaces (for example: `StartupInitializer`, `ImportProvisioner`, `TransitionPublisher`) and pass concrete dependencies through constructors; keep per-test stubs at interface granularity instead of dozens of callback fields.",
